Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.52,0:00:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Essential Hayek \N 欢迎来到哈耶克简要
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.14,0:00:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Don Boudreaux \N 我是Don Boudreaux
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.14,0:00:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,professor of economics at George Mason University \N 乔治梅森大学经济学教授
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.74,0:00:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,senior fellow with the Fraser Institute \N 弗雷泽研究所高级研究员
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.70,0:00:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and blogger at Café Hayek \N 博客Café Hayek的博主之一
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.70,0:00:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This video was part of the Fraser Institute initiative \N 本视频是由弗雷泽研究所制作的
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.10,0:00:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to present the key ideas of F.A. Hayek in an easily accessible format \N 对哈耶克关键思想的通俗介绍
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.40,0:00:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In this video, we explore one of Hayek's best know ideas \N 本视频将介绍哈耶克最著名的一个思想
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.44,0:00:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and perhaps his most profound insight \N 可能也是他最重要的洞见
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.22,0:00:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the role of prices in conveying information \N 价格在传递信息中的作用
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.94,0:00:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All economists understand that people make decision based on the cost they face \N 经济学家都明白人们基于面临的成本
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.30,0:00:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and the benefits they expect to receive \N 和预期收益做出决策
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.30,0:00:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,In most cases \N 多数情况下
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.30,0:00:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the key cost of the decision is the price the person faces to purchase a good or service \N 决策的主要成本是个体为商品或服务所支付的价格
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.40,0:00:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This idea is complex, so let's simplify it with an example \N 这个观点有点复杂，所以让我们举个栗子
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.40,0:00:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Sara \N 这是Sara
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.40,0:00:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Sara loves coffee \N 她爱喝咖啡
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.40,0:00:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and prefers Columbian coffee \N 尤其喜欢哥伦比亚咖啡
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.40,0:00:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,which she buys from her local grocery store \N 她在本地的杂货店购买咖啡
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.48,0:01:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The local store usually sells her favorite coffee to her for 10 dollars \N 她最爱的咖啡一般卖10美金
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.88,0:01:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Sara doesn't know any of the details or cost \N Sara并不了解关于咖啡生产的成本和细节
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.60,0:01:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of how the coffee beans are grown \N 例如咖啡豆是怎么种植的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.60,0:01:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the irrigation of the coffee farm \N 咖啡田的灌溉方法
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.60,0:01:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,how the beans are roasted \N 如何烘焙咖啡豆
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.60,0:01:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,or how the coffee is transported to her store \N 咖啡是怎么运到杂货店的等等
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.88,0:01:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,all she knows is her favorite Columbian coffee costs 10 dollars \N 她只知道她最爱喝的哥伦比亚咖啡卖10美金
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.18,0:01:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and that it's worth to her given the enjoyment she gets from drinking Columbian coffee \N 并且与她喝咖啡所获得的愉悦相比，这10美金花的值得
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.38,0:01:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but what happens if bad weather in Columbia severely damages the coffee farm field \N 不过如果哥伦比亚天气变差，咖啡种植地被毁，将会如何？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.42,0:01:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,bad weather and crop damage been fewer coffee beans from Columbian \N 变差的天气和损毁的咖啡植株意外着更少的哥伦比亚咖啡豆
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.18,0:01:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and that results in the price of Columbia coffee going up \N 这将导致哥伦比亚咖啡的价格上涨
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.86,0:01:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so when Sara next goes to her local grocery store \N 所以当Sara下次去杂货店时
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.86,0:01:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,she finds the price of her favorite Columbian coffee is now 20 dollars \N 她发现她最爱的哥伦比亚咖啡现在要卖20美金了
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.86,0:01:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Sara doesn't know why the price went up, nor did she need to know why \N Sara既不知道、也不需要知道为什么咖啡涨价了
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.32,0:01:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The increased price sends her a signal that prompts her to make an informed decision \N 上升的价格促使Sara基于新价格重新做出决定
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.34,0:02:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,She can pay 20 dollars for her favorite Columbian coffee \N 她可以为最爱的咖啡付20块
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.58,0:02:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but, the higher price of the Columbian coffee \N 不过，哥伦比亚咖啡的价格越高
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.38,0:02:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,means that she will have to give up more something else to buy that coffee \N 意味着她为了买咖啡将不得不更多地放弃购买其他东西
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.88,0:02:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, Sara is likely voluntarily choose to buy another type of coffee \N 事实上，Sara很可能会自愿去购买另一种
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.80,0:02:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,one perhaps even at a lower price than a normal Columbian coffee \N 比哥伦比亚咖啡便宜的咖啡
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.80,0:02:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,say, Indonesian coffee, which costs 9 dollars \N 比如只要9美金的印尼咖啡
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.36,0:02:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,so even though Sara doesn't have any of the information about why the price of Columbian coffee changed \N 所以即使Sara完全不知道为什么哥伦比亚咖啡的价格上涨了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.08,0:02:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,she makes the same decision based purely on the change in price she observes in her grocery store \N 她仅仅依靠店里标价做出的决定
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.80,0:02:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that she would have made had she known that a weather disaster in Columbian destroyed that much of that country's coffee crop \N 与假如她知道哥伦比亚咖啡减产做出的决定会是一致的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.78,0:02:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What Hayek explained and clarified is that people make decisions as if \N 哈耶克阐明的正是人们做出的决策就好像
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.34,0:02:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,they have incredible amount of information about why the price of good or service is what it is \N 他们掌握价格变动背后的大量信息一样
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.54,0:02:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,when in fact, they have little or no information about why the price is what it is \N 但其实他们对价格为何如此一无所知
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.98,0:03:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They simply know what the price is and that is sufficient \N 仅仅知道价格是多少
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.38,0:03:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to prompt each of us to act as if we know vast quantities of facts \N 就已经足以使人们像掌握了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.74,0:03:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,about economics reality that we can't possibly really know \N  其实根本无力掌握的大量经济信息那样作出决策
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.56,0:03:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,To learn more and download <Essential Hayek> for free \N 想要下载和更多了解《哈耶克简要》
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.88,0:03:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,visit www.essentialhayek.org \N 请访问www.essentialhayek.org
